# Stack Guardrails

Any change to a locked row needs an **ADR + eng lead**. Do not “just try” an alternate.

## Locked

| Layer | Use this | Not this |
|---|---|---|
| Language | TypeScript strict | Untyped JS as default |
| Web | Next.js **App Router** | CRA, Vite-as-primary, new Pages Router routes |
| API | NestJS modular monolith | FastAPI/Django/Flask primary |
| Data | Prisma + PostgreSQL | Mongo, second ORM (TypeORM/Drizzle/…) |
| Cache/jobs | Redis + BullMQ | Redis as business DB; fire-and-forget hacks |
| UI | Tailwind + shadcn/ui + Radix | MUI / Ant / Chakra as primary |
| Forms/validate | Zod + RHF | Ad-hoc untyped forms |
| Client server-state | TanStack Query | Redux/MobX as default |
| Motion | GSAP + `@gsap/react` (Soft Gift story) | Animate everything; Framer only for tiny UI |
| Money | `*Paise: Int` (or Decimal) | JS `number` float rupees |
| Packages | pnpm workspaces | npm/yarn drift without ADR |
| API shape | REST `/api/v1` | Unversioned public APIs |

## OK without ADR

`clsx`, `tailwind-merge`, `sonner`, Helmet/security middleware, pino/structured logs, payment/email SDKs **behind adapters**, **one** of date-fns | luxon repo-wide.

## Instant reject

Secrets in git · cross-module table queries · microservices-by-default · `any` to silence TS · LMS vocabulary models · copying prototype CRA/FastAPI/Mongo into production paths.
